Neural Network Plot and Results

Results

Of the 10 features that correlated most with a song popularity, the year, artist, title, and dB of a song contributed most to a songs popularity. For model comparison, the ensemble method (Random Forest) achieved a lower RMSE than the neural network. The Random Forest achieved a lower RMSE than the neural network by roughly 1 point. This was due to the Random Forest better at capturing the non-linear relationships.
